III. Play Style & Macro-Movements:

Unlike traditional card games, your "deck" can physically shift across the board.
Environmental Shifting: Playing an Ecology 3E Card by allows you to "Slide" entire clusters of cards to the left or right. This is used to dodge incoming "Single Stream" attacks or to align a flank.
Economic Pivoting: Economic 3E Cards allow you to "Rotate" or "Re-channel" your deck’s internal flow. This shifts your offensive pressure from one lane to another without moving the cards themselves.
The Tug-of-War: Once a bridge is formed, the game enters a high-speed state where players fight for "Throughput." The goal is to push your color stream into the opponent's Energy Cube by adding more cards that connect to the sides or removing certain conditions to make your self more efficient via removing defensive plots.

